               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; the name of the protagonist; the name of the donor and his relatives and the scribe and his relatives.&#xD;
A few lines, divided into several groups, alternating with black lines, in the incipit pages of Texts I, II, III, IV, in the incipit page of the “Discourse on the origin of the genealogy of St. George” in Text I, in the incipit pages of the monthly sections in Text II and in incipit of Text V; incipit of each miracle; the initial words of some paragraphs; some corrections (words or letters) interlineally; elements of the punctuation signs and Ethiopic numerals.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- For Text I, s. EAE II, 764a, IV, 945a.</note>
                     <note>- For Text II (Gädlä Giyorgis), cp. BGeorge.</note>
                     <note>- For Text IV (Täʾamrä Giyorgis), cp. BGeorge (119-66) and V.ARRAS, Miraculorum s. Georgii Megalomartyris collectio altera, Louvain 1953 (CSCO 139; SAe 32).</note>
                     <note>- Text II contains the colophon of the work (fols. 79vb-80va, cp. BGeorge, 274-76): [fol. 79vb] ወሶበ፡ ፈጸመ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡ ገድሎ፡ አነ፡ ሰቅራጥስ፡ ገብሩ፡ [fol. 80ra] ለጊዮርጊስ፡ ኮንኩ፡ አትልዎ፡ ለእግዚእየ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡ በኵሉ፡ {ገድሉ}፡ ወፃማሁ፡ ወለካልሁ፡ ዘንተ፡ ጸሐፍኩ፡ … [fol. 80rb] ተፈጸመ፡ እንዘ፡ ንነግድ፡ ብሔረ፡ ቈስጠንጢኖስ፡ መካን፡ ዘስሙ፡ ቍስቋስ፡ መርስ፡ እንዘ፡ ንነግድ፡ ወአስተዳሎኩ፡ ዘንተ፡ መጽሐፈ። ወኮነ፡ በዘአዕረፈ፡ እግዚእየ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡ ሃብሩ፡ ለኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ በዘተከለለ፡ ወርኁ፡ በጽርዕ፡ ጵንፍልዮ፡ ስሙ፡ ወትርጓሜሁ፡ ወርኃ፡ ሚያዝያ፡ አመ፡ ፳ወ፫ለሠርቅ፡ ወዕለቱሂ፡ ዓርብ፡ በጊዜ፡ ፱ሰዓት፡ አሜን።</note>
                     <note>ሃሌ፡ ሉያ፡ ተተርጐመት፡ ዛቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ አምሳነ፡ ዓረቢ፡ በግዕዝ፡ በአፈ፡ ሚካኤል፡ {ዘይንዕስ} ፡ወልደ፡ ወልዱ፡ ለአባ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡ ወልደ፡ አባ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ጳጳስ። … [fol. 80va] … ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን፡ ወአሜን፡ ለይኩን፡ ለይኩን፡</note>
                     <note>The author of the text, whose name is Pasicrates (Säqraṭǝs), the servant of St. George, says that he finished this work while they were travelling in the country of Constantinople to a place called “Qwǝsqwas Märs”, where St. George’s martyrdom took place on the 23th of Miyazya (cp. BGeorge, 274-75).</note>
                     <note>The note states that the text was translated from Arabic into Gǝʿǝz by Michael “the younger”, the grandson of ʾabba George, son of ʾabba Michael the Bishop (cp. BGeorge, 275).</note>
                     <note>- The miracles (Text IV) are not numbered, except Miracles 1, 48 and 60. Miracles 48 and 60 are wrongly numbered as 20 and 33.</note>
                     <note>- All quires are quinians.</note>
